Surf_ofrenda made for ksf halloween
I did have the full time for this one but I had the worst flu of my life for two months straight during and my entire house had to be rewired so I could only work for short periods of time, I wish I could have done more but I am very happy with what I achieved.
This map became something very personal to me, and is a way of honouring a cat I grew up with and loved dearly.

Day of the Dead is a celebration that honours the souls of those who have passed away but are still remembered. It is believed that on this day, these souls return to Earth to be with their loved ones once more. To help guide these souls back home, people set up ofrendas at their homes and at gravesites. These ofrendas are decorated with photographs, items that the deceased enjoyed while alive as well as their old personal belongings. People also play music and enjoy delicious food as part of the celebration. Marigolds are an important symbol during Day of the Dead. They are believed to help lead departed souls back to their loved ones with their bright colours and powerful aroma.
